<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Once you add a custom header on the Zend_Mail object, there's no way to remove it.</p>

<p>For example:</p>

<p>$mail = new Zend_Mail();
$mail-&gt;addHeader('List-Unsubscribe', 'somevalue');</p>

<p>There's no way to remove the List-Unsubscribe header.</p>

<p>You could provide public clearHeader($headerName) and proxy it to protected _clearHeader($headerName) method.</p>

<p>Then you could remove the List-Unsubscribe header already set usig
$mail-&gt;clearHeader('List-Unsubscribe');</p>

<p>I'm willing to provide a patch with unit test, if the suggestion is accepted.</p>

    </div>
